#Aurangzeb is instrumental music performed on the stage of Coke Studio by Mughal-e-Funk and the super talented Coke Studio house band. Produced & Directed by Zohaib Kazi and Ali Hamza

Kami Paul, Farhan Ali, Rakae Jamil, Rufus Shahzad

snippet.title: Coke Studio Season 11| Apna Gham| Bilal Khan & Mishal Khawaja
snippet.description:
Coke Studio Season 11| Episode 8
#ApnaGham captures the feeling of falling in love again. Bilal Khan presents a funky soundscape along with the soulful vocals of Mishal Khawaja, who was discovered through Instagram and made her way to Coke Studio Explorer. 
Bilal Khan, recently started a vlog and is part of many Pakistani top singers. He has sung songs like Larho Mujhe, Lamhay, Bachana and Taaray. For Coke Studio Season 11 he’ll be performing Apna Gham with the talented Mishal Khawaja to make it to the list of new love songs of 2018. #CokeStudio11

snippet.title: Coke Studio Season 11| Wah Jo Kalaam| Asrar Shah, Shamu Bai & Vishnu
snippet.description:
Coke Studio Season 11| Episode 8
#WahJoKalaam establishes the Sindhi soul vibe in the voice of Asrar, who previously sang a few Coke Studio songs such as Shakar Wandan Re, Aakho Ali Ali and Gaddiye. Accompanied by Shamu Bai and Vishnu’s powerful vocals, this brother-sister duo used to sing bhajan in Sindhi and performed at local festivals before being discovered by Coke Studio Explorer and making their way to Coke Studio Season 11! This trio is going to be a unique addition to the best of folk-rock music and new Sindhi songs of 2018. #CokeStudio11

Produced & Directed by Zohaib Kazi and Ali Hamza

Lyrics by
Asrar Shah

Composed by
Ustad Sultan Ahmed

snippet.title: Coke Studio Season 11| Ya Qurban| Khumariyaan
snippet.description:
Coke Studio Season 11| Episode 7
#YaQurban, a Pashto song, is the perfect reflection of Pakhtun music by Khumariyaan. Rubab, in conversation with percussion assembles a distinctive beat producing a splendid rhythmic pattern for instrumental music.
Khumariyaan has performed twice on Coke Studio Season 11, starting from Rasha Mama – a calming song representing folk Pashto music to their new song fusing folk rock, Ya Qurban. Hopefully their tracks using Pashto Saazand Rubab music will make it to the top folk rock songs of 2018. #CokeStudio11

Produced & Directed by Zohaib Kazi and Ali Hamza

snippet.title: Coke Studio Season 11| Ballay Ballay| Abrar Ul Haq and Aima Baig
snippet.description:
Coke Studio Season 11| Episode 7
#BallayBallay is a Punjabi mash-up of the desi wedding songs by Abrar Ul Haq and Aima Baig. The track has been masterfully created by the house band featuring a strong groove improvised around mehndi songs for dancing and Pakistani shaadi songs.
Just like his many hits, this will make it to the list of Abrar Ul Haq’s top songs and top mehndi songs for dancing performed on the Coke Studio Season 11 stage. #CokeStudio11
